Script logtracer --------------------------------------------------------------------------

You can find different messages on /var/log/messages throug the following sentence:

"refused|invalid|error|fail|lost|shut|down|offline"

That is useful in order to find error messages. You can change the word and the file in order to find derterminate patern in a file. 

Script 

logger command ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

With logger command, you can write into the logs.. 

logger -t error "Test entry"

This command record the logs with an entry error with the message Test entry.

nohup command -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Nohup, short for no hang up is a command in Linux systems that keep processes running even after exiting the shell or terminal.

Nohup PREVENTS the processes or jobs from receiving the SIGHUP (Signal Hang UP) signal. This is a signal that is sent to a process upon closing or exiting the terminal. In this guide, we take a look at the nohup command and demonstrate how it can be used.

Examples:

#nohup /root/logtail &
$nohup ./myscript.sh &



